reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for my small narrow laundry room/entryway
reviews.reviewText: The shoe stand is a lifesaver for our narrow laundry that we use as our entryway from the garage. It efficiently solves our problem of keeping our shoes organized and out of the way before entering the home. Its compact design fits perfectly in this limited space, and fits multiple pairs of shoes. Feels sturdy and looks fine. Overall, it's a practical and space-saving solution that has made our daily routine much smoother

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for tight spaces
reviews.reviewText: Given the tight open space in my closet, the vertical orientation was just what I needed. The spaces for the shoes (10 W) were adequate, as long as I put them in the slots sideways to begin with.The rack was very easy to put together, requiring minimal time and using just the provided tool. It was not the sturdiest item I have seen but certainly adequate, and for how reasonable the price was it was well worth it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact and functional
reviews.reviewText: This is really the perfect solution for what I needed it for. I am in limited space with a basic reach-in closet available for clothes and accessories. I already have a shoe shelf on the floor of the closet that is full, as is the floor space around it. I needed a way to tidy up how I stored my athletic shoes. This shelving unit is perfect. Assembly was fairly easy. Some of the threads inside the support poles weren’t “clean” and the double-ended connectors wouldn’t “catch.” I had to route them out using a screw and the included Allen key. Once I did that, I could resume assembly. Minor inconvenience. Start to finish it took me about 1/2 hour to complete. The finish is a true dark brown and blends well with the walnut chest of drawers beside it. 9.5/10

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for small spaces!
reviews.reviewText: This is exactly what I was looking for! I do not wear shoes in my home as I was raised in an extremely European household, so this fixes my problem of where to put my shoes now that I live in an apartment. This product is super lightweight, looks good, and is easy to assemble. Not only is it easy to assemble, but it's easy to customize as well! I actually left a row off when assembling it so it would be a little shorter than the dimensions listed on the website are. I use the very top of the unit as a place to put my keys and mail, the second shelf for dog leashes, and the rest of the shelves for shoes. One thing I will note is that it does not fit women's boots/heels very well. I have to lay my at an angle/sideways to get two to fit per row, but it doesn't bother me that much. I also have a boot mat that I've placed right under the unit and that extend to the side of it to place shoes I've just worn/wear frequently/are dirty or wet. It's not the most sturdy product on the market, but for the price I would purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Locker stack for golf shoes
reviews.reviewText: Easy to assemble and fit inside my locker. I would by this product again if need!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing durability and perfect for small area.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my husbands shoes and boots. I read a ton of reviews on many shoe racks and this is really as good as other buyers said. The wood is solid and metal is sturdy. I left off one level because we didn’t need it. The best feature is that the toes of my husbands shoes and boots can come out the other side to allow shoes to rest evenly on the shelf area. Large shoes are the biggest problem for shoe racks and this one has solved the issue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It is a great product, easy to assemble, almost flawless except on their quality control side: one of the polls needed to construct had some plastic over-run covering the hole and preventing the screw from attaching. I had to scrap out that area, not easy, by pounding with a hammer and using small chisel to clean out enough of the plastic to allow the screw to enter..... that was a bit difficult. They should probably send one extra poll and one extra double side screw in case there is another quality control oversight. Had I not been able to break off the extra plastic covering the hole I would have had to return the shoe rack, and missed out on this fabulous product design, which I absolutely LOVE!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Wouldn’t use for shoe rack but great for shelves!
reviews.reviewText: I initially ordered a different brand that was similar to this one and it was so easy to put together fit my husband size 14 shoe and was small and took up no space I thought I should buy one for shelves in my extremely small laundry room. My washer and dryer are black so I found this one. The price was similar and I didn’t think much of it. However compared to my other one it is much smaller, was harder to put together, and much shorter and smaller. Honestly this isn’t great for a shoe rack, maybe for children’s shoes but it’s so small. And it’s not black it’s a dark brown. However, I bought it to use for shelves in my small laundry room and it is perfect for that. Takes up hardly any room and perfect for what I needed it for except it isn’t black. If you purchase this for shelving or a child’s shoe rack this will work but my other one I purchased is a far better shoe rack.
Solid, easy to assemble. Will see how it stands over the next year but overall great for utilizing space

The slabs are glued together, they are inseparable despite trying all means. The ones which are not stuck together and are seperate have scratches and marks...as can be seen in the pictures.Unfortunately I opened the parcel to assemble it after return window closed, now totally unusable and donot know what to do with it. Total waste of money.
